The paper discusses the evaluation of deep reinforcement learning (RL) agents, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus is on the design of high-quality environments for experimental evaluation, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) aspects. Additionally, the paper mentions the ability to perform a wide range of experiments and analyses, which suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) component.
